<article><h2 id=3D"what_is_monotonic_function">What Is Monotonic Function?<=
/h2>
<p>To understand Spearman=E2=80=99s rank correlation, it is important to un=
derstand monotonic function. A monotonic function is one that either never =
increases or never decreases as its independent variable changes.</p>
<p>The following graph illustrates the monotonic function:</p>
<p style=3D"text-align: center;"><img src=3D"https://www.simplilearn.com/ic=
e9/free_resources_article_thumb/Spearman%E2%80%99s_Rank_Correlation_1.jpg" =
alt=3D"Spearman's_Rank_Correlation_1" width=3D"512" height=3D"288" class=3D=
"blend-mode"></p>
<ul><li aria-level=3D"1">Monotonically Increasing: As the variable X increa=
ses, the variable Y never decreases.</li>
<li aria-level=3D"1">Monotonically Decreasing: As the variable X increases,=
 the variable Y never increases.</li>
<li aria-level=3D"1">Not Monotonic: As the X variable increases, the Y vari=
able sometimes decreases and sometimes increases.&nbsp;</li>
</ul></article><article><h2 id=3D"spearmans_rank_correlation">Spearman=E2=
=80=99s Rank Correlation</h2>
<p>Spearman=E2=80=99s rank correlation measures the strength and direction =
of association between two ranked variables. It basically gives the measure=
 of monotonicity of the relation between two variables i.e. how well the re=
lationship between two variables could be represented using a monotonic fun=
ction.</p>
<p>The formula for Spearman=E2=80=99s rank coefficient is:</p>
<p style=3D"text-align: center;"><img src=3D"https://www.simplilearn.com/ic=
e9/free_resources_article_thumb/Spearman%E2%80%99s_Rank_Correlation_2.png" =
alt=3D"Spearman's_Rank_Correlation_2." width=3D"396" height=3D"165" class=
=3D"blend-mode"></p>
<p>=F0=9D=9D=86 =3D Spearman=E2=80=99s rank correlation coefficient</p>
<p>di =3D Difference between the two ranks of each observation</p>
<p>n =3D Number of observations</p>
<p>The Spearman Rank Correlation can take a value from +1 to -1 where,</p>
<ul><li aria-level=3D"1">A value of +1 means a perfect association of rank<=
/li>
<li aria-level=3D"1">A value of 0 means that there is no association betwee=
n ranks</li>
<li aria-level=3D"1">A value of -1 means a perfect negative association of =
rank</li>
</ul><p>Let=E2=80=99s understand the concept better with the help of an exa=
mple.</p>
<p></p><div banner-id=3D"63524daa01c5470f648b4571" index=3D"1" class=3D"eng=
agingBanner"><div class=3D"detail-info-banner"><div class=3D"left-clm"><h4>=
Master Gen AI Strategies for Businesses with</h4><span class=3D"discription=
">Generative AI for Business Transformation Program</span><a href=3D"https:=
