></div><div class=3D"right-clm"><img class=3D"blend-mode" width=3D"16" heig=
ht=3D"9" src=3D"https://www.simplilearn.com/ice9/banners/free_resources_ban=
ners/lead_banners/GenAI_For_Business.png" alt=3D"Master Gen AI Strategies f=
or Businesses with"></div></div></div><p></p>
</article><article><h2 id=3D"example_of_spearmans_rank_correlation">Example=
 of Spearman=E2=80=99s Rank Correlation</h2>
<p>Consider the score of 5 students in Maths and Science that are mentioned=
 in the table.</p>
<p style=3D"text-align: center;"><img src=3D"https://www.simplilearn.com/ic=
e9/free_resources_article_thumb/Spearman%E2%80%99s_Rank_Correlation_3.png" =
alt=3D"Spearman's_Rank_Correlation_3" width=3D"312" height=3D"228" class=3D=
"blend-mode"></p>
<p>Step 1: Create a table for the given <a href=3D"https://www.simplilearn.=
com/what-is-data-article" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener" title=3D"data"=
>data</a>.</p>
<p>Step 2: Rank both the data in descending order. The highest marks will g=
et a rank of 1 and the lowest marks will get a rank of 5.</p>
<p>Step 3: Calculate the difference between the ranks (d) and the square va=
lue of d.</p>
<p>Step 4: Add all your d square values.</p>
<p style=3D"text-align: center;"><img src=3D"https://www.simplilearn.com/ic=
e9/free_resources_article_thumb/Spearman%E2%80%99s_Rank_Correlation_4.png" =
alt=3D"Spearman's_Rank_Correlation_4" width=3D"512" height=3D"210" class=3D=
"blend-mode"></p>
<p>Step 5: Insert these values into the formula.</p>
<p style=3D"text-align: center;"><img src=3D"https://www.simplilearn.com/ic=
e9/free_resources_article_thumb/Spearman%E2%80%99s_Rank_Correlation_5.png" =
alt=3D"Spearman's_Rank_Correlation_5." width=3D"396" height=3D"165" class=
=3D"blend-mode"></p>
<p>=3D 1 - (6 * 14) / 5(25 - 1)</p>
<p>=3D 0.3</p>
<p>The Spearman=E2=80=99s Rank Correlation for the given data is 0.3. The v=
alue is near 0, which means that there is a weak correlation between the tw=
o ranks.</p>
